## Why does any of this matter?

This is obviously a simplified version of the PageRank algorithm and PageRank is just one of the many, very secretive tools that Google uses today. Not to mention AI recommendations.

However, having an idea of how this works behind the scenes can help us look more sceptically at the suggestions offered to us by search engines, social media apps and AI chatbots.

If we search for an expert on a topic, a candidate for a job opening, or a hot take on a breaking news story are we seeing a real mix of people with diverse backgrounds and opinions or are the same old popular accounts popping up over and over again?

